    <|unfolded-io-text>
      <subsection*|Rotation Matrix Conjugation><label|rotation-matrix-conjugation>

      Let <math|u> and <math|v> be rotation matrices in <math|\<bbb-R\><rsup|2>>:\ 

      <\equation*>
        u=<matrix|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|cos \<theta\><rsub|u>>|<cell|-sin \<theta\><rsub|u>>>|<row|<cell|sin \<theta\><rsub|u>>|<cell|cos \<theta\><rsub|u>>>>>>,<space|1em>v=<matrix|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|cos \<theta\><rsub|v>>|<cell|-sin \<theta\><rsub|v>>>|<row|<cell|sin \<theta\><rsub|v>>|<cell|cos \<theta\><rsub|v>>>>>>
      </equation*>

      <subsubsection*|Step-by-Step Geometric Interpretation><label|step-by-step-geometric-interpretation>

      The transformation <math|u<rsup|-1>*v*u> applied to a vector <math|x> proceeds as follows:\ 

      <\enumerate>
        <assign|labelenumi|<macro|<number|<enumi-nr>|arabic>.>>

        <item><with|font-series|bold|mode|math|u*x>: Rotate <math|x> by angle <math|\<theta\><rsub|u>> in the standard coordinate system

        <item><with|font-series|bold|mode|math|v*<around|(|u*x|)>>: Apply rotation <math|v> to the result, rotating by angle <math|\<theta\><rsub|v>>

        <item><with|font-series|bold|mode|math|u<rsup|-1>*<around|(|v*u*x|)>>: Apply the inverse rotation <math|u<rsup|-1>>, which rotates by <math|-\<theta\><rsub|u>>
      </enumerate>

      <subsubsection*|Net Effect><label|net-effect>

      The composition <math|u<rsup|-1>*v*u> represents a rotation by angle <math|\<theta\><rsub|v>> about a different axis. Specifically, it rotates by <math|\<theta\><rsub|v>> around the direction that was originally rotated by <math|u>.\ 

      <subsubsection*|Algebraic Verification><label|algebraic-verification>

      Since rotation matrices commute, we have:\ 

      <\equation*>
        u<rsup|-1>*v*u=u<rsup|-1>*u*v=v
      </equation*>

      This shows that for rotation matrices in <math|\<bbb-R\><rsup|2>>, conjugation doesn't change the transformation - it remains a rotation by <math|\<theta\><rsub|v>>. The geometric interpretation becomes more meaningful in higher dimensions or with non-commuting transformations.\ 

      <subsubsection*|Key Insight><label|key-insight>

      The conjugation <math|u<rsup|-1>*v*u> expresses the same rotation <math|v> but in a coordinate system that has been rotated by <math|u>. The net rotation angle remains <math|\<theta\><rsub|v>>, but the “frame of reference” for describing the rotation has changed.\ 
    </unfolded-io-text>

